task-id - String - (filter by task ID). `task-id` format: e386471f-139a-4e59-877f-50ece8135b99.
task-state - String - (filter exactly by task status). Valid values: `0` (initial), `1` (running), `2` (succeeded), `-1` (failed).
task-sql-keyword - String - (filter fuzzily by SQL statement keyword, such as `DROP TABLE`).
task-operator- string (filter by sub-UIN)

members.document: The name of the target data source. To grant admin permission, it must be `*` (all resources at this level); to grant data source and database permissions, it must be `COSDataCatalog` or `*`; to grant table permissions, it can be a custom data source; if it is left empty, `DataLakeCatalog` is used. Note: To grant permissions on a custom data source, the permissions that can be managed in the Data Lake Compute console are subsets of the account permissions granted when you connect the data source to the console.

Admin: `ALL` (default); data connection: `CREATE`; database: `ALL`, `CREATE`, `ALTER`, and `DROP`; table: `ALL`, `SELECT`, `INSERT`, `ALTER`, `DELETE`, `DROP`, and `UPDATE`.
